-- Turkish Troops Kill 26 PKK Militants in Southeast, Sabah Reports
-- B y   S e l c a n   H a c a o g l u
-- 2012-09-11T06:43:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-11/turkish-troops-kill-26-pkk-militants-in-southeast-sabah-reports.html
Turkish troops killed 26 militants
of the Kurdistan Workers’ Party, or PKK, in clashes in the
country’s southeast, Sabah reported, without saying where it
obtained the information.  Seven Turkish soldiers were wounded in the clashes that
took place near the town of Semdinli in Hakkari province, which
borders Iran and  Iraq , according to the Istanbul-based paper. It
didn’t say when the clashes occurred.  The PKK has been fighting for autonomy in  Turkey ’s Kurdish-
dominated southeast since 1984.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcan Hacaoglu in Ankara at 
 shacaoglu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
